cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL

The paper describes a language for modeling complex domains using Bayesian networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of object-oriented programming concepts suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and the reuse of probabilistic models across different objects and classes suggests a focus on databases (cs.DB) and programming languages (cs.PL).
